headline: Hewlett Packard, NetApp Better Positioned To Sidestep Tariff Headwinds Ahead of Earnings: Analyst
summary: JP Morgan analyst Samik Chatterjee shared earnings previews for several prominent hardware companies, cautioning that these firms may contend with ongoing demand uncertainty and renewed tariff risks in their upcoming earnings reports. Chatterjee sees another round of conservative results in the coming week, with stock movements more likely to reflect how investors interpret management’s efforts to either de-risk the second half of the year or contain expectations for potential full-year downside
